Japanese Bought Net 304 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-06-29T23:54:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/japanese-bought-net-304-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended June 24 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 304 billion yen ($3.8 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 49.3 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 13.8 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 339.6 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 978.7 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 31.8 billion yen in stocks, and sold 46.8 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 1057.3
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  